Following the {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離令|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (the separation of Shinto and Buddhism), the deities were relocated from the original {{ill|Miyama Shrine|ja|御山神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to the current Sanki-dō.

=== Origin ===
It is believed that the revered monk {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (also known as Kōbō Daishi) enshrined Sanki Daigongen in 806 CE (Daido 1) when he founded Mount Misen as a sacred site.

