The three deities of Sanki Daigongen are: * '''Tsuichō Kishin (追帳鬼神)''': A deity governing the virtue of "fortune and virtue" (福徳), with {{ill|Dainichi Nyorai|ja|大日如来|1=Vairocana|lt=Dainichi Nyorai|2=ja|3=大日如来|4=zh|5=毗卢遮那佛|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dainichi Nyorai|13=User:Immanuelle/Vairocana|qq=}} as the {{ill|honji-butsu|ja|本地仏|1=Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|lt=Honji Buddha|2=ja|3=本地垂迹|4=fr|5=Honji suijaku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/honji-butsu|13=User:Immanuelle/Honji_suijaku#Honji Buddha|qq=}} (original Buddha). * '''Jibi Kishin (時眉鬼神)''': A deity overseeing the virtue of "wisdom" (知恵), with {{ill|Kokūzō Bosatsu|ja|虚空蔵菩薩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kokūzō Bosatsu|qq=}} as the honji-butsu. Kokūzō Bosatsu is also the principal deity enshrined at {{ill|Misen Main Hall|ja|弥山本堂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Misen Main Hall|qq=}}. * '''Mara Kishin (魔羅鬼神)''': A deity associated with the virtue of "subjugation" (降伏), with {{ill|Fudō Myōō|ja|不動明王|1=Acala|lt=Fudō Myōō|2=ja|3=不動明王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fudō Myōō|lt=Fudō Myōō|1=Acala|2=ja|3=不動明王|13=User:Immanuelle/Acala|qq=}} as the honji-butsu.
Following the {{ill|Shinbutsu Bunri|ja|神仏分離令|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinbutsu Bunri|qq=}} (the separation of Shinto and Buddhism), the deities were relocated from the original {{ill|Miyama Shrine|ja|御山神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyama Shrine|qq=}} to the current Sanki-dō.
=== Origin === It is believed that the revered monk {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kūkai|qq=}} (also known as Kōbō Daishi) enshrined Sanki Daigongen in 806 CE (Daido 1) when he founded Mount Misen as a sacred site.
=== Mantra === The mantra associated with Sanki Daigongen is: * '''On Aratan Nō Un Sowaka''' (オン・アラタンノウ・ウン・ソワカ).
Additionally, there are {{ill|wasan|ja|和讃|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/wasan|qq=}} (Buddhist hymns) praising the virtues of Sanki Daigongen. == See Also == * {{ill|List of Buddhas|ja|仏の一覧|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/List of Buddhas|qq=}} * {{ill|Gongen|ja|権現|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gongen|qq=}} * {{ill|Daitengu|ja|大天狗|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daitengu|qq=}} * {{ill|Mountain worship|ja|山岳信仰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mountain worship|qq=}} * {{ill|Mitaki-dera|ja|三瀧寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitaki-dera|qq=}} * {{ill|Guhin|ja|狗賓|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Guhin|qq=}}
